    <statement><p>The pie chart represents a school<rsq/>s student population.</p>
<!-- PTX:WARNING: PGML wanted to center align here. -->
<image xmlns:pi="http://pretextbook.org/2020/pretext/internal" pi:generated="webwork/images/section-fraction-arithmetic-8-2-15-image-1.png" width="83%"/>
<p><fillin characters="10" name="AnSwEr0001"/> more of the school is white students than black students.</p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>{\frac{1}{4}}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>By the pie chart, the school has <m>{{\frac{5}{12}}}</m> white students, and <m>{{\frac{1}{6}}}</m> black students.</p>
<p>We will use subtraction to find the difference:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}[t]
   \amp \phantom{{}=}{{\frac{5}{12}}}-{{\frac{1}{6}}} \\
   \amp = \frac{5 \cdot 1}{12 \cdot 1} - \frac{1 \cdot 1}{6 \cdot 1} \\
   \amp = \frac{5}{12} - \frac{2}{12} \\
   \amp = \frac{5-2}{12} \\
   \amp = \frac{3}{12} \\ \amp = \frac{1}{4} \\
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
</solution>
